is\u003C/strong\u003E and the \u003Cstrong\u003Eflexor carpi radialis\u003C/strong\u003E. This anatomical relationship is important for accessing the radial artery for procedures such as arterial blood sampling or cannulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPalmaris longus\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located more medially and does not border the radial artery\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexor carpi ulnaris\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located on the ulnar side of the forearm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPronator teres\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located proximally and medially in the forearm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPronator quadratus\u003C/strong\u003E - This muscle is located deep in the distal forearm\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The radial artery in the forearm runs between the brachioradialis and the flexor carpi radialis.","Understanding the anatomical relationships of the radial artery is important for procedures like arterial blood sampling and cannulation."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Raszewski JA, Black AC, Launico MV, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Hand Compartments. [Updated 2023 Oct 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/books/NBK532942/","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. A